The following are two explanations on why individuals conform: People adhere to other people's beliefs or habits in order to fit in and be accepted by a group. People comply to a group's stated or tacit rules or expectations in order to fulfill social standards and avoid undesirable repercussions. Normative impact happens regardless of the ambiguity of the information. Conformity is influenced by three factors: Larger groups tend to have greater social effect on individuals. Individuals are more prone to comply when there is group unity. People are more prone to adhere to the beliefs or practices of a group that they believe to be of high status or respect. 